path.aria-label: Each Hole is organized by color (according to the ofcial scorecard) Each Hole is organized by color (according to the ofcial scorecard) ALL PAR 4s & PAR 5s will have dots in the fairway corresponding with a 250 yard drive from the associated tee box. So a WHITE dot in the farway means thats where a 250 yard drive would have landed from the BACK of the white teeboox A BLUE dot in the farway means thats where a 250 yard drive would have landed from the BACK of the blue teeboox A BLACK dot in the farway means thats where a 250 yard drive would have landed from the BACK of the black teeboox
Holes that have an X show CARRY distance to the X
